<item>
            <title>[SOLR-2108] ReversedWildcardFilter can create false positives</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2108</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Reported from the userlist: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&quot;For instance, the query *zemog* matches documents that contain Gomez&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.lucidimagination.com/search/document/35abfdabfcec99b7/false_matches_with_reversedwildcardfilterfactory&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.lucidimagination.com/search/document/35abfdabfcec99b7/false_matches_with_reversedwildcardfilterfactory&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12473516">SOLR-2108</key>
            <summary>ReversedWildcardFilter can create false positives</summary>
